FWIW, I use this little function to recurse into Python objects returned by the boto3 DynamoDB resource layer and convert any Decimal values to ``int`` or ``float``.  It is by no means foolproof and doesn't in any way solve the problem of lack of precision in Python's float type but it solves my problems which is mainly to turn the data into something that can be returned to API Gateway via a Python Lambda function.

```python
def replace_decimals(obj):
    if isinstance(obj, list):
        for i in xrange(len(obj)):
            obj[i] = replace_decimals(obj[i])
        return obj
    elif isinstance(obj, dict):
        for k in obj.iterkeys():
            obj[k] = replace_decimals(obj[k])
        return obj
    elif isinstance(obj, decimal.Decimal):
        if obj % 1 == 0:
            return int(obj)
        else:
            return float(obj)
    else:
        return obj

