[Here](https://github.com/GalSim-developers/GalSim/blob/%23691/examples/great3/cgc.yaml) is my first pass at cgc.yaml.  The main thing I discovered that isn't implemented currently that we need for this is the ability to keep the same PSF and shear for a bunch of objects in a row before generating a new one.  I think a convenient API for this is to allow any gsobject or value item to take a `repeat: N` parameter, which means repeat each result N times before moving on to the next one.  It shows up here in both the psf and the galaxy.shear.  

