@jeffbloo @linkerzhang @shschaefer @dzhulgakov How about we move the schema instantiation from global static variables to a function static variable in the `map()` function? i.e. something like:
```
class SchemasRegisterer {
  SchemasRegisterer() {
   // AUTOGENERATED BEGIN
    _map.insert(std::make_pair("Aaa", OperatorSchema(Aaa)....));
    ...
   _map.insert(std::make_pair("Zzz", OperatorSchema(Zzz)....));
   // AUTOGENERATED END
  }
}

Map* map() {
  static auto SchemasRegisterer{};
  return _map
}
```
This way we only do the initialization at the first usage time, and there is no need for an Init and it's thread safe.

To achieve this we will need to move the source of truth of the schemas to say yaml files (instead .cc files) and then have a script to auto-generate the chunk between `AUTOGENERATED BEGIN` and `AUTOGENERATED END` above.

